<figure><img src="http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2874/12894322004_1d69a7df79_c.jpg" alt="The sky"><figcaption></figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3727/12893914635_f96ae96335_c.jpg" alt="An alley"><figcaption></figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2894/12894034433_234b99e424_c.jpg" alt="Moto Taxis"><figcaption>There are tons of these around. It makes me wonder if the same person is making them. </figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3821/12894046343_75413bde83_c.jpg" alt="Statue"><figcaption>In the center of San Ignacio</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7304/12893959425_98d2ba64de_c.jpg" alt="Market Back"><figcaption>Behind the market</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3720/12893975455_b83cb0621b_c.jpg" alt="Road in shambles"><figcaption>This was just after I passed into Peru. It made me appreciate the street sweeper in San Francisco.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3667/12894416014_dc4bbff954_c.jpg" alt="Peru Border"><figcaption>This was the border. The Brown building was Immigration, the two stacked containers were customs.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7296/12894112023_8bcbd6f875_c.jpg" alt="The Road"><figcaption>Almost to Peru in this photo, looks like there might be some rain ahead.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3800/12894470344_93ce34c832_c.jpg" alt="Ecuadorian Army"><figcaption>The stopped me to log my documents. I took a sneaky photo.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2829/12894517054_ee874390de_c.jpg" alt="Selfie"><figcaption>Less sneaky photo while they look at my docs.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7435/12894533614_a6d9d3e61b_c.jpg" alt="Dirty Motorcycle"><figcaption>As you can see it was a very muddy day.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2862/12894120485_542e4e3f96_c.jpg" alt="Small Town"><figcaption>I stopped in this town to get lunch. I think you can pretty much see the whole town in this photo. There were a bunch of kids running around with water guns, and they've decided that traffic is less of a priority than volleyball. Bravo.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7383/12894238303_092ab0451b_c.jpg" alt="Dirty Motorcycle"><figcaption>I was just as dirty.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm8.staticflickr.com/7349/12894597984_d6ff648d07_c.jpg" alt="Water Crossing"><figcaption>This was one of the smaller water crossings. There were probably about 15 today. Many of which were tiny, but a few gave me a run for my money.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm4.staticflickr.com/3787/12894607744_ab56ba6897_c.jpg" alt="Blue Gas"><figcaption>This is the gas station up in the mountains. As you can see, they filter the gas with a child's sock.</figcaption></figure><figure><img src="http://farm3.staticflickr.com/2823/12894636724_d1d8fc76dd_c.jpg" alt="Gas Pump"><figcaption>Here's the gas pump. One gallon per pale.</figcaption></figure>